This paper deals with expert systems and uncertain inference, which are topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of multidimensional contingency tables and joint probabilities also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and statistical inference (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper involves calculations and manipulation of data, which could fall under data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) or software engineering (cs.SE).
